<br>
When she assaults an enemy with her magic, she is not driven by an emotion or goal.  She is not thrilled when the enemy falls before her and dies at her feet.  She sees it as one less enemy to fight later in life, one less obstacle in her path...<br>
<br>
&quot;You're mad!  You're crazy!&quot;  <br>
<br>
She began cutting selective meats from the corpse and put them in her pouch.  &quot;Why do you say that?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You killed one of your own kind.&quot;<br>
<br>
Aluveal turned her head, looking at the elf over her shoulder.  &quot;He was weak, he served no purpose.  He is nothing but food.&quot;<br>
<br>
The elf was struck with horror at the thought.  &quot;You... you would eat... your own kind?&quot;<br>
<br>
Aluveal climbed to her feet and turned to face the elf, cocking her head to one side.  &quot;Wouldn't you?  They are quite tasty.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I am no cannibal!&quot;<br>
<br>
Aluveal shrugged.  &quot;And while you starve looking for roots in a barren land, I'll have the nourishment I need to do what it is that must be done.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;And what is it that must be done?&quot;<br>
<br>
Aluveal smirked at the elf.  &quot;Now if I told you that... it would ruin the surprise later, wouldn't it?&quot;  She walked past the elf, wrinkling her nose at it's smell.  &quot;Little bit of seasoning and over a fire, you'd smell pretty damn good.&quot; the gasps from the elf amusing her, yes this could be a fun game indeed.<br>
<br>
